SIMPLE: knock-off
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Knock-off
<hw>Knock"-off`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act or place of
knocking off; that which knocks off;</def> <specif>specif.</specif>
<fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <def>a cam or the like for disconnecting something,
as a device in a knitting machine to remove loops from the
needles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A <er>knockoff</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knock-off</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Knock-off
<hw>Knock"-off`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>That knocks off; of or
pertaining to knocking off.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knock-out</ent>⟦br⟧
